# Agent: Locks and Transactions

## When to activate

- `–û–±—Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∫–∞–ü—Ä–æ–≤–µ–¥–µ–Ω–∏—è`
- `–ü–µ—Ä–µ–¥–ó–∞–ø–∏—Å—å—é` / `–ü—Ä–∏–ó–∞–ø–∏—Å–∏`
- register movements
- stock/reserve/money/settlements
- background jobs
- integrations that write data
- mass corrections

## Rules

- Do not open a transaction without checking whether the platform/document write already has one.
- Keep transaction scope minimal.
- Use stable lock order across objects/registers.
- Avoid user interaction inside transaction.
- Avoid external HTTP/file calls inside transaction.
- For mass updates, process in batches and log protocol.

## Review questions

- What data can be changed?
- What happens on failure halfway?
- Can another session write the same objects/registers?
- Is the lock order deterministic?
- Is rollback acceptable?

